jparsec.io

Class CatalogRead

  • java.lang.Object
    • jparsec.io.CatalogRead

  • public class CatalogRead
extends java.lang.Object
    Performs file and parameter reading operations. This class supports JPL and COLOGNE database of molecular spectroscopy.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    T. Alonso Albi - OAN (Spain)

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> readJPLtransitions(java.lang.String mol,
                                                       double limit_temp)
                                                                throws JPARSECException
        Read JPL molecule transitions file.
        Parameters:
        mol - Molecule file name.
        limit_temp - Temperature limit to search for transitions. Only transitions with upper level energy below this value will be returned. 0 will return all transitions.
        Returns:
        Strings with the list of transitions.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - Thrown if the method fails.

      • readJPLtransitions

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> readJPLtransitions(java.lang.String mol,
                                                       double limit_temp,
                                                       double limit_rint)
                                                                throws JPARSECException
        Read JPL molecule transitions file.
        Parameters:
        mol - Molecule file name.
        limit_temp - Temperature limit to search for transitions. Only transitions with upper level energy below this value will be returned. 0 will return all transitions.
        limit_rint - Minimum value of the rint parameter of the transition, which is associated with the intensity of the line. Set to 0 to avoid this condition.
        Returns:
        Strings with the list of transitions.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - Thrown if the method fails.

      • getTransitions

        public static java.lang.String[] getTransitions(java.lang.String transition,
                                java.lang.String name,
                                boolean jpl_cat,
                                double width)
                                         throws JPARSECException
        Gets a string with the data of certain transitions. If the molecule has more than maxTransitions transitions, and the required one is after that number, returning string will be an empty string.
        Parameters:
        transition - Transition name or frequency as given in the catalog.
        name - Name of the molecule as given in the catalog.
        jpl_cat - True for JPL catalog, false for COLOGNE.
        width - Width in MHz to return all transitions at frequency around (+/-) (width/2).
        Returns:
        The transitions found. The first one is the reference one.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • getTransitions

        public static java.lang.String[] getTransitions(java.lang.String transition,
                                java.lang.String name,
                                boolean jpl_cat,
                                double width,
                                double limit_temp,
                                double limit_rint)
                                         throws JPARSECException
        Gets a string with the data of certain transitions. If the molecule has more than maxTransitions transitions, and the required one is after that number, returning string will be an empty string.
        Parameters:
        transition - Transition name or frequency as given in the catalog.
        name - Name of the molecule as given in the catalog.
        jpl_cat - True for JPL catalog, false for COLOGNE.
        width - Width in MHz to return all transitions at frequency around (+/-) (width/2).
        limit_temp - Temperature limit to search for transitions. Only transitions with upper level energy below this value will be returned. 0 will return all transitions.
        limit_rint - Minimum value of the rint parameter of the transition, which is associated with the intensity of the line. Set to 0 to avoid this condition.
        Returns:
        The transitions found. The first one is the reference one.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.

      • getTransitions

        public static java.lang.String[] getTransitions(double frec0,
                                java.lang.String name,
                                boolean jpl_cat,
                                double width,
                                double limit_temp,
                                double limit_rint)
                                         throws JPARSECException
        Gets a string with the data of certain transitions. If the molecule has more than maxTransitions transitions, and the required one is after that number, returning string will be an empty string.
        Parameters:
        frec0 - Transition frequency in MHz.
        name - Name of the molecule as given in the catalog.
        jpl_cat - True for JPL catalog, false for COLOGNE.
        width - Width in MHz to return all transitions at frequency around (+/-) (width/2).
        limit_temp - Temperature limit to search for transitions. Only transitions with upper level energy below this value will be returned. 0 will return all transitions.
        limit_rint - Minimum value of the rint parameter of the transition, which is associated with the intensity of the line. Set to 0 to avoid this condition.
        Returns:
        The transitions found. The first one is the reference one.
        Throws:
        JPARSECException - If an error occurs.
